{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RkEJGU3bRAB1iyEqZLGEmf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Let me now create a comprehensive inventory report:\n\n## Inventory Report: Frontend Coinflip Integration and Tests\n\n### 1. **`sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`** — Exported Functions\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`**\n\n| Function | Line | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|------|-----------|---------|\n| `getMatchPda` | 31 | `(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number]` | Derives the PDA for a match given the creator's public key |\n| `getConfigPda` | 38 | `(): [PublicKey, number]` | Derives the Coinflip config PDA (singleton) |\n| `onChainMatchToUI` | 126 | `(matchPda: PublicKey, data: OnChainMatch): UIMatch` | Converts on-chain match account data to frontend UI type |\n| `fetchAllOpenMatches` | 167 | `async (connection: Connection): Promise<UIMatch[]>` | **Queries all \"waiting\" phase matches on-chain** (main lobby query) |\n| `fetchMatchByCreator` | 183 | `async (connection: Connection, creator: PublicKey): Promise<UIMatch \\| null>` | **Per-user query: fetches active match for a specific creator** (used on wallet connect) |\n| `fetchMatch` | 199 | `async (connection: Connection, matchPda: PublicKey): Promise<UIMatch \\| null>` | Fetches a single match by PDA (used for polling updates) |\n| `buildCreateMatchInstruction` | 215 | `(creator: PublicKey, tier: Tier, side: CoinSide): { instruction: TransactionInstruction; matchPda: PublicKey }` | Builds `createMatch` instruction (not fully async-safe) |\n| `buildCreateMatchTx` | 242 | `async (connection: Connection, creator: PublicKey, tier: Tier, side: CoinSide): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey }>` | Builds complete `createMatch` transaction |\n| `buildJoinMatchTx` | 272 | `async (connection: Connection, opponent: PublicKey, matchCreator: PublicKey): Promise<Transaction>` | Builds `joinMatch` transaction with Orao VRF accounts |\n| `buildCancelMatchTx` | 310 | `async (connection: Connection, creator: PublicKey): Promise<Transaction>` | Builds `cancelMatch` transaction for Waiting-phase matches |\n| `buildTimeoutCancelTx` | 333 | `async (connection: Connection, caller: PublicKey, matchCreator: PublicKey, opponent: PublicKey): Promise<Transaction>` | Builds `timeoutCancel` transaction (after deadline, VRF unfulfilled) |\n| `buildClaimPayoutTx` | 363 | `async (connection: Connection, caller: PublicKey, matchCreator: PublicKey, opponent: PublicKey): Promise<Transaction>` | Builds `claimPayout` transaction (either player can trigger) |\n\n**Key Interfaces (lines 77–96):**\n- `RoundPhaseVariant` (line 78): Anchor enum variants — `{ waiting: {} } | { active: {} } | { locked: {} } | { resolving: {} } | { settled: {} } | { refunded: {} }`\n- `OnChainMatch` (line 81): On-chain account structure with `creator`, `opponent`, `tier`, `entryAmount`, `phase`, `claimed`, `vrfRequestKey`, etc.\n\n**Important:** \n- **NO \"claimable\" or \"unresolved\" query functions exist** — the design uses simple per-match polling instead.\n- `fetchMatchByCreator` (line 183) is the **only per-user query function** — it fetches the creator's single active match by deriving the PDA.\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches` (line 167) returns **all \"waiting\" phase matches** (not filtered by user).\n\n---\n\n### 2. **`sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`** — Test Suite\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`**\n\n#### Test Hierarchy\n\n| Test Suite | Line | Tests | What They Verify |\n|-----------|------|-------|------------------|\n| `describe(\"initialize_config\")` | 359 | 1 test | Config initialization with treasury and paused flag |\n| `describe(\"create_match\")` | 378 | 3 tests | Match creation, escrow, validation |\n| `describe(\"join_match\")` | 460 | 3 tests | Join transitions, self-join rejection, double-join rejection |\n| `describe(\"claim_payout\")` | 553 | 8 tests | Winner/loser payouts, fee distribution, profile updates, security |\n| `describe(\"cancel_match\")` | 792 | 3 tests | Cancellation in Waiting phase, rejection after Locked, authorization |\n| `describe(\"timeout_cancel\")` | 854 | 3 tests | Permissionless timeout refund, deadline validation, VRF fulfillment check |\n| `describe(\"full lifecycle\")` | 933 | 3 tests | End-to-end workflows |\n\n#### Detailed Test List\n\n**initialize_config (line 359–373):**\n- `it(\"creates config with treasury and paused=false\")` (line 360): Verifies config account created with authority, treasury, and paused flag\n\n**create_match (line 378–455):**\n- `it(\"creates match in Waiting phase with correct escrow\")` (line 379): Checks phase, tier, side, escrow amount\n- `it(\"escrows correct lamport amount\")` (line 395): Verifies rent + entry amount deducted\n- `it(\"rejects invalid side\")` (line 414): Enforces side enum bounds (0–1)\n- `it(\"rejects invalid tier\")` (line 435): Enforces tier enum bounds\n\n**join_match (line 460–548):**\n- `it(\"transitions to Locked, doubles escrow, sets VRF fields\")` (line 461): Checks phase, opponent, escrow, VRF request key, deadline\n- `it(\"rejects self-join\")` (line 486): Prevents creator from joining own match\n- `it(\"rejects join when already Locked\")` (line 513): Prevents double-join\n\n**claim_payout (line 553–787):**\n- `it(\"creator wins with HEADS, fee to treasury\")` (line 554): Tests winner receives payout, treasury gets fee\n- `it(\"opponent wins with TAILS\")` (line 582): Tests opponent winner path\n- `it(\"either player can trigger claim — payout goes to derived winner\")` (line 610): **Key: claim is permissionless; winner derived on-chain from VRF**\n- `it(\"match PDA closed after claim\")` (line 634): Verifies PDA closed post-settlement\n- `it(\"rejects claim with unfulfilled randomness\")` (line 648): Enforces VRF fulfillment check\n- `it(\"rejects double claim (account closed)\")` (line 666): Prevents double-settlement\n- `it(\"rejects unauthorized caller (not creator or opponent)\")` (line 685): **Only creator or opponent can call**\n- `it(\"updates player profiles via CPI — creator wins\")` (line 726): Verifies on-chain stats updated (totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon)\n- `it(\"updates player profiles via CPI — opponent wins\")` (line 757): Verifies loser stats also updated\n\n**cancel_match (line 792–849):**\n- `it(\"creator cancels Waiting match, full refund\")` (line 793): Verifies escrow + rent returned\n- `it(\"rejects cancel after Locked (CannotCancel)\")` (line 811): Enforces Waiting-only phase\n- `it(\"rejects cancel by non-creator\")` (line 827): Only creator can cancel\n\n**timeout_cancel (line 854–928):**\n- `it(\"permissionless refund after deadline when VRF unfulfilled\")` (line 855): **Permissionless! Third party can trigger**\n- `it(\"rejects timeout before deadline\")` (line 892): Enforces deadline check\n- `it(\"rejects timeout when VRF IS fulfilled — must claim instead\")` (line 909): Enforces VRF unfulfilled check\n\n**full lifecycle (line 933–1009):**\n- `it(\"create → join → claim(HEADS) → PDA closed\")` (line 934): End-to-end happy path with HEADS win\n- `it(\"create → cancel → create again\")` (line 966): Tests PDA reuse after cancellation\n- `it(\"create → join → timeout (VRF unfulfilled) → both refunded\")` (line 985): Timeout refund path\n\n---\n\n### 3. **`sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`** — Claim/Cancel/Join Flow\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`**\n\n#### Context Type (lines 78–107)\n\n| Property | Type | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| `activeMatch` | `UIMatch \\| null` | Current match user is in |\n| `openMatches` | `UIMatch[]` | All \"waiting\" phase matches |\n| `userHistory` | `UIMatch[]` | Placeholder (always empty array, line 123) |\n| `creating` | `boolean` | Transaction in flight |\n| `joining` | `boolean` | Transaction in flight |\n| `claiming` | `boolean` | Transaction in flight |\n| `joiningMatchId` | `string \\| null` | Which match is being joined |\n\n#### Action Methods\n\n| Method | Lines | Implementation |\n|--------|-------|-----------------|\n| **`createMatch`** | 231–287 | Pre-checks if match already exists (line 246), builds tx (line 262), sends + confirms (line 269), fetches created match from on-chain (line 275) |\n| **`joinMatch`** | 289–335 | Fetches match PDA (line 301), extracts creator (line 308), builds tx (line 309), sends + confirms (line 315), sets activeMatch (line 323) |\n| **`cancelMatch`** | 337–352 | Builds cancel tx (line 345), sends + confirms (line 346), clears activeMatch (line 347) |\n| **`timeoutCancel`** | 354–381 | Requires activeMatch with opponent (lines 359–362), builds tx with creator + opponent (line 369), sends + confirms (line 375), clears activeMatch (line 376) |\n| **`claimPayout`** | 385–419 | **Permissionless claim** — caller (either player) + creator + opponent (lines 398–405), sends + confirms (line 408), sets dismissal flag (line 411), clears activeMatch (line 412) |\n\n#### Polling & State Management\n\n| Feature | Lines | Details |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| **activeMatch polling** | 180–220 | Polls every 2–5s; faster (2s) when `phase === \"ready\"` (VRF awaiting) |\n| **Phase animation** | 197–205 | Intercepts `ready → complete`, inserts `flipping` phase for 3s (line 199–205) |\n| **dismissedMatchRef** | 143, 411, 426 | Prevents in-flight polls from restoring a dismissed match (race condition protection) |\n| **Wallet connect hook** | 434–448 | Calls `fetchMatchByCreator` on wallet connect (line 436) to restore active match |\n\n#### Error Parsing (lines 27–76)\n\nConverts Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages:\n- Line 31: \"Wallet not connected\"\n- Line 36: \"User rejected\" / \"Transaction cancelled\"\n- Line 41: \"Insufficient funds\"\n- Line 46: \"You already have an active match\" (account in use)\n- Line 51: Network errors\n- Line 56–61: Anchor errors (InvalidPhase, CannotJoinOwnMatch)\n- Line 64: \"Transaction simulation failed\"\n- Line 69: \"Blockhash expired\"\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Search Results: \"claimable\", \"unresolved\", \"per-user\"**\n\n**Finding:** No results found for these terms in the coinflip frontend code.\n\n- **No `claimable` or `unresolved` query function exists** — the design does not have a dedicated \"pending settlement\" or \"claimable games\" list.\n- **No per-user history query** — `userHistory` is hardcoded as empty (line 123).\n- **Only per-user function:** `fetchMatchByCreator` (chain.ts:183) — fetches the single active match for a wallet.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Count | Key Functions/Tests |\n|--------|-------|-------------------|\n| **chain.ts exports** | 12 | Query: `fetchAllOpenMatches`, `fetchMatchByCreator`, `fetchMatch`; Build: `buildCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, `buildCancelMatchTx`, `buildTimeoutCancelTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx` |\n| **coinflip.ts test suites** | 7 | initialize_config, create_match, join_match, claim_payout, cancel_match, timeout_cancel, full_lifecycle |\n| **coinflip.ts total tests** | 23 | 1 + 3 + 3 + 8 + 3 + 3 + 3 |\n| **Context actions** | 5 | createMatch, joinMatch, cancelMatch, timeoutCancel, claimPayout |\n| **Per-user queries** | 1 | `fetchMatchByCreator` (line 183) — single active match |\n| **Claimable/unresolved queries** | 0 | N/A — not implemented |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0e4d3b3b0f991d86 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57576\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 55277</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"2593b286-4f14-4894-acf7-f41a2084b7dd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Inventory the frontend coinflip integration and tests:\n\n1. Read `sources