{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCnwmKL5R3hGdBEGcCWnVk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive inventory report.\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Program Comprehensive Inventory\n\n### STATE.RS STRUCTURES & EVENTS\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`**\n\n#### CoinflipConfig (Lines 6-17)\n- **PDA Seed**: `[b\"coinflip_config\"]` (singleton)\n- **Fields**:\n  - `authority: Pubkey` (line 10) — Admin authority who can update config\n  - `treasury: Pubkey` (line 12) — Fee destination wallet\n  - `paused: bool` (line 14) — Whether game is paused (rejects new matches)\n  - `bump: u8` (line 16) — Bump seed for PDA derivation\n- **Constraints**: `#[derive(InitSpace)]` allows Anchor space calculation\n\n#### CoinflipMatch (Lines 21-52)\n- **PDA Seed**: `[b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]` (one active match per creator)\n- **Fields**:\n  - `creator: Pubkey` (line 25) — Player who created the match\n  - `opponent: Pubkey` (line 27) — Player who joined; `Pubkey::default()` if empty\n  - `tier: u8` (line 29) — Tier index (0-5: Iron, Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum, Diamond)\n  - `entry_amount: u64` (line 31) — Entry amount in lamports (derived from tier)\n  - `creator_side: u8` (line 33) — Side chosen by creator (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails)\n  - `phase: RoundPhase` (line 35) — Shared lifecycle enum (`Waiting` → `Locked` → `Settled`/`Refunded`)\n  - `result: u8` (line 37) — Winning side after VRF resolution (0 or 1; only valid when settled)\n  - `winner: Pubkey` (line 39) — Winner's pubkey; `Pubkey::default()` until settled\n  - `claimed: bool` (line 41) — Whether payout has been claimed\n  - `created_at: i64` (line 43) — Unix timestamp when match was created\n  - `locked_at: i64` (line 45) — Unix timestamp when match entered LOCKED phase (0 if still WAITING)\n  - `resolve_deadline: i64` (line 47) — Deadline for VRF resolution; after this, timeout refund available\n  - `vrf_request_key: Pubkey` (line 49) — Address of Orao randomness PDA for VRF lookup at claim time\n  - `bump: u8` (line 51) — Bump seed for PDA derivation\n\n#### MatchSettled Event (Lines 55-63)\n- **Emitted by**: `claim_payout` handler\n- **Fields**:\n  - `creator: Pubkey` (line 57)\n  - `opponent: Pubkey` (line 58)\n  - `winner: Pubkey` (line 59)\n  - `randomness: [u8; 32]` (line 60) — Raw VRF randomness from Orao\n  - `payout_amount: u64` (line 61) — Amount paid to winner\n  - `fee_amount: u64` (line 62) — Amount sent to treasury\n\n---\n\n### ERROR.RS - ERROR CODES\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/error.rs`**\n\nAll errors defined at lines 3-52:\n\n| Error Code | Code Value | Line | Message |\n|-----------|-----------|------|---------|\n| InvalidSide | 6100 | 7 | Invalid side: must be 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails) |\n| InvalidTier | 6101 | 11 | Invalid tier index |\n| InvalidPhase | 6102 | 15 | Match is not in the expected phase |\n| InsufficientFunds | 6103 | 19 | Insufficient funds for entry amount |\n| CannotJoinOwnMatch | 6104 | 23 | Creator cannot join their own match |\n| UnauthorizedOracle | 6105 | 27 | Only the oracle authority can resolve matches |\n| AlreadyClaimed | 6106 | 31 | Payout has already been claimed |\n| NotWinner | 6107 | 35 | Only the winner can claim the payout |\n| CannotCancel | 6108 | 39 | Match can only be cancelled in WAITING phase |\n| VrfRequestFailed | 6109 | 43 | VRF randomness request failed |\n| LockTimeoutNotElapsed | 6110 | 47 | Lock timeout has not elapsed yet |\n| UnauthorizedCaller | 6111 | 51 | Only the creator or opponent can cancel a timed-out match |\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: INITIALIZE_CONFIG\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/initialize_config.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 5-22)\n```rust\npub struct InitializeConfig<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub authority: Signer<'info>,  // Line 9: Admin authority who initializes config\n\n    #[account(\n        init,\n        payer = authority,\n        space = 8 + CoinflipConfig::INIT_SPACE,\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 19: Config PDA (singleton)\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,  // Line 21\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 24-32)\n1. Line 26: Set config authority to transaction signer\n2. Line 27: Set treasury address from parameter\n3. Line 28: Initialize paused flag to false\n4. Line 29: Store PDA bump seed\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions\nNone (no require! checks)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\nNone\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: CREATE_MATCH\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/create_match.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 11-35)\n```rust\npub struct CreateMatch<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: Signer<'info>,  // Line 15: Player creating the match\n\n    #[account(\n        init,\n        payer = creator,\n        space = 8 + CoinflipMatch::INIT_SPACE,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()],\n        bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,  // Line 25: Match PDA\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 32: Config PDA (read-only for pause check)\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,  // Line 34\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 37-72)\n1. **Line 39**: Check game not paused via `check_not_paused(false, config.paused)`\n2. **Line 41**: Validate side is 0 or 1 via `is_valid_side(side)`\n3. **Line 43**: Get tier amount from tier index via `get_tier_amount(tier)`\n4. **Lines 46-51**: Transfer entry_amount from creator to match PDA via `transfer_lamports_to_pda()`\n5. **Line 53**: Get current Unix timestamp via `Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp`\n6. **Lines 56-69**: Initialize CoinflipMatch account fields:\n   - creator, opponent (Pubkey::default)\n   - tier, entry_amount, creator_side\n   - phase = RoundPhase::Waiting\n   - result = 0, winner = Pubkey::default, claimed = false\n   - created_at, locked_at = 0, resolve_deadline = 0\n   - vrf_request_key = Pubkey::default, bump\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 41**: `InvalidSide` — side must be 0 or 1\n- **Line 43**: `InvalidTier` — tier index out of bounds (0-5)\n- Implicit: **Line 39**: `GamePaused` (via shared `check_not_paused`)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::constants::is_valid_side`** (line 2 import, line 41 call) — Validates side ∈ {0, 1}\n- **`rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_to_pda`** (line 3 import, lines 46-51 call) — Deposits creator's entry amount to match PDA\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 4 import) — Enum for phase tracking\n- **`rng_shared::pause::check_not_paused`** (line 5 import, line 39 call) — Checks game not paused\n- **`rng_shared::tiers::get_tier_amount`** (line 6 import, line 43 call) — Maps tier index to lamport amount\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: JOIN_MATCH\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 11-52)\n```rust\npub struct JoinMatch<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: Signer<'info>,  // Line 15: Opponent joining the match\n\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,  // Line 23: Match PDA to join\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 30: Config PDA\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    pub orao_program: UncheckedAccount<'info>,  // Line 34: Orao VRF program\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_network_state: UncheckedAccount<'info>,  // Line 39: Orao network state PDA\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_treasury: UncheckedAccount<'info>,  // Line 44: Orao treasury for VRF fee payment\n\n    /// CHECK: Orao VRF CPI validates and initializes this account.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_random: UncheckedAccount<'info>,  // Line 49: Orao randomness account (created by Orao CPI)\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,  // Line 51\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 54-99)\n1. **Line 58**: Validate phase transition from Waiting → Locked via `lifecycle::transition()`\n2. **Lines 61-64**: Require opponent ≠ creator\n3. **Line 66**: Get entry_amount from match\n4. **Line 67**: Get opponent's pubkey\n5. **Lines 70-75**: Transfer entry_amount from opponent to match PDA via `transfer_lamports_to_pda()`\n6. **Line 78**: Use match PDA key as 32-byte seed for VRF request\n7. **Lines 79-87**: Request Orao VRF via `vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness()` with seed\n8. **Line 90**: Get current Unix timestamp\n9. **Lines 91-96**: Update match state:\n   - opponent = opponent_key\n   - phase = RoundPhase::Locked\n   - locked_at = now\n   - resolve_deadline = now + DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (120 seconds)\n   - vrf_request_key = orao_random's pubkey\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 58**: `InvalidPhase` — phase must be Waiting; via `lifecycle::transition()` returns `LifecycleError::InvalidTransition`\n- **Lines 61-64**: `CannotJoinOwnMatch` — opponent cannot be creator\n- Implicit: **Line 79**: `VrfRequestFailed` (if Orao CPI fails)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_to_pda`** (line 2 import, lines 70-75 call) — Deposits opponent's entry amount\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::transition`** (line 3 import, line 58 call) — Validates Waiting → Locked transition\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 3 import) — Enum for phase\n- **`rng_shared::timeout::DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`** (line 4 import, line 95 call) — 120 seconds\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness`** (line 5 import, lines 79-87 call) — CPI into Orao VRF to request randomness\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: CLAIM_PAYOUT\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/claim_payout.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 11-66)\n```rust\npub struct ClaimPayout<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub caller: Signer<'info>,  // Line 15: Either creator or opponent can trigger claim\n\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,  // Line 24: Match PDA (closed after claim; rent → creator)\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 31: Config PDA (for treasury address + CPI signing)\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated against config.treasury in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub treasury: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 36: Treasury account to receive fees\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.creator in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 41: Creator account (receives rent refund on close)\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.opponent in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 46: Opponent account\n\n    /// CHECK: Key validated against coinflip_match.vrf_request_key; data read by shared VRF helper.\n    pub randomness_account: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 50: Orao randomness PDA\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 55: Creator's player profile PDA (platform program)\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 60: Opponent's player profile PDA (platform program)\n\n    pub platform_program: Program<'info, platform::program::Platform>,  // Line 63: Platform program for CPI calls\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,  // Line 65\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 68-178)\n1. **Lines 72-76**: Validate phase == Locked and not claimed\n2. **Lines 79-83**: Require caller is creator or opponent\n3. **Lines 86-101**: Validate all accounts match stored state (treasury, creator, opponent, randomness_account)\n4. **Line 104**: Read Orao randomness via `read_orao_randomness()` (rejects if not fulfilled)\n5. **Line 107**: Derive result (coin side) from randomness[0] via `from_randomness()`\n6. **Lines 108-112**: Determine winner based on whether result matches creator_side\n7. **Line 115**: Calculate pool = entry_amount × 2\n8. **Line 116**: Calculate fee and net payout via `calculate_net_payout()` (pool - fee)\n9. **Lines 120-126**: Transfer payout to winner and fee to treasury via `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`\n10. **Line 129**: Get config bump for signer seeds\n11. **Lines 133-142**: CPI call to platform program to update creator profile via `update_player_profile_cpi()`:\n    - wins_delta = 1 if creator is winner, else 0\n    - total_wagered_delta = entry_amount\n    - total_won_delta = payout if creator is winner, else 0\n12. **Lines 144-153**: CPI call to platform program to update opponent profile via `update_player_profile_cpi()`:\n    - wins_delta = 1 if opponent is winner, else 0\n    - total_wagered_delta = entry_amount\n    - total_won_delta = payout if opponent is winner, else 0\n13. **Lines 156-163**: Emit MatchSettled event with creator, opponent, winner, randomness, payout_amount, fee_amount\n14. **Lines 168-172**: Update match state:\n    - phase = RoundPhase::Settled\n    - claimed = true\n    - result = result coin side\n    - winner = winner pubkey\n15. **Line 174**: Account is closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint; rent sent to creator\n\n#### Events Emitted\n- **MatchSettled** (lines 156-163): creator, opponent, winner, randomness, payout_amount, fee_amount\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 74**: `InvalidPhase` — phase must be Locked\n- **Line 76**: `AlreadyClaimed` — claimed flag must be false\n- **Lines 81-83**: `UnauthorizedCaller` — caller must be creator or opponent\n- **Lines 88, 92, 96, 100**: `InvalidPhase` (reused) — treasury, creator, opponent, randomness_account keys must match stored values\n- **Line 104**: `VrfError::RandomnessNotFulfilled` — Orao randomness must be fulfilled\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::constants::from_randomness`** (line 2 import, line 107 call) — Derives coin side (0 or 1) from randomness[0] via `byte % 2`\n- **`rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda`** (line 3 import, lines 125-126 call) — Transfers payout to winner and fee to treasury\n- **`rng_shared::fees::calculate_net_payout`** (line 4 import, line 116 call) — Splits pool into (fee, net_payout); fee = pool × 300 bps / 10000\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 5 import) — Enum\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::read_orao_randomness`** (line 6 import, line 104 call) — Reads 32-byte randomness from Orao randomness account; errors if not fulfilled\n- **`rng_shared::cpi::update_player_profile_cpi`** (line 133, 144 calls) — CPI to platform program to update player profiles with game stats (wager_amount, won_amount, is_winner)\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: CANCEL_MATCH\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/cancel_match.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 7-23)\n```rust\npub struct CancelMatch<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: Signer<'info>,  // Line 11: Creator cancelling their match\n\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,  // Line 20: Match PDA (closed on cancel; escrow + rent → creator)\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,  // Line 22\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 25-39)\n1. **Lines 30-33**: Require phase == Waiting (can only cancel before opponent joins)\n2. **Line 35**: Account closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint; all lamports (escrow + rent) returned to creator\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 32**: `CannotCancel` — phase must be Waiting; Locked matches use timeout_cancel instead\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 2 import) — Enum\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: TIMEOUT_CANCEL\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/timeout_cancel.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 10-38)\n```rust\npub struct TimeoutCancel<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub caller: Signer<'info>,  // Line 14: Any signer (permissionless after deadline)\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.creator.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 19: Creator account; receives entry refund + rent\n\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.opponent.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 24: Opponent account; receives entry refund\n\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,  // Line 33: Match PDA (closed after refunds; rent → creator)\n\n    /// CHECK: Key validated against coinflip_match.vrf_request_key; data read by shared VRF helper.\n    pub randomness_account: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 37: Orao randomness PDA (checked to verify VRF NOT fulfilled)\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 40-88)\n1. **Lines 44-47**: Require phase == Locked\n2. **Lines 50-55**: Validate creator and opponent accounts match stored keys via `require_keys_eq!` macro\n3. **Lines 57-62**: Check that resolve_deadline has expired via `is_expired(resolve_deadline, now)`\n4. **Lines 67-70**: Check that VRF randomness is NOT fulfilled:\n   - Attempt to read randomness via `read_orao_randomness()`\n   - If fulfilled and non-zero, reject with `InvalidPhase` (must use claim_payout instead)\n   - If not fulfilled or read fails, proceed with timeout refund\n5. **Line 72**: Get entry_amount from match\n6. **Lines 75-77**: Refund both players their entry amounts via `transfer_lamports_from_pda()` twice\n7. **Lines 80-82**: Transition phase to Refunded via `lifecycle::transition()` and update match state\n8. **Line 84**: Account closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint; remaining lamports (rent) returned to creator\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 46**: `InvalidPhase` — phase must be Locked\n- **Lines 50-55**: `require_keys_eq!` (Anchor macro) — creator and opponent keys must match stored values\n- **Line 61**: `LockTimeoutNotElapsed` — resolve_deadline must have elapsed (now >= deadline)\n- **Line 70**: `InvalidPhase` (reused) — VRF must NOT be fulfilled (if fulfilled, use claim_payout instead)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda`** (line 2 import, lines 76-77 calls) — Refunds both players' entry amounts\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::transition`** (line 3 import, line 80 call) — Validates Locked → Refunded transition\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 3 import) — Enum\n- **`rng_shared::timeout::is_expired`** (line 4 import, line 60 call) — Returns true if now >= resolve_deadline\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled`** (line 5 import, line 68 call) — Returns true if randomness is non-zero (fulfilled)\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::read_orao_randomness`** (line 5 import, line 67 call) — Reads randomness from Orao account; errors if not fulfilled\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: FORCE_CLOSE\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/force_close.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 8-28)\n```rust\npub struct ForceClose<'info> {\n    pub authority: Signer<'info>,  // Line 11: Config authority (admin)\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n        has_one = authority,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 19: Config PDA; validates authority via has_one\n\n    /// CHECK: The match account to close. Not deserialized — may have old layout.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub match_account: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 23: Match account to close (may be corrupted/undeserializable)\n\n    /// CHECK: Receives the lamports. Should be the match creator or admin.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub recipient: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 27: Recipient for drained lamports\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 30-45)\n1. **Line 34**: Verify match_account is owned by this program (coinflip program ID)\n2. **Line 37**: Get lamports balance from match_account\n3. **Line 38**: Drain all lamports from match_account to recipient\n4. **Line 42**: Zero the match_account's data to effectively close it\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 34**: `require_keys_eq!` — match_account.owner must be coinflip program ID (crate::ID)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\nNone (admin utility; no shared functions)\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE: SHARED CRATE FUNCTION USAGE\n\n| Shared Function | Module | Instructions Using It | Purpose |\n|-----------------|--------|----------------------|---------|\n| `is_valid_side()` | constants | create_match | Validates side ∈ {0, 1} |\n| `from_randomness()` | constants | claim_payout | Derives coin side from randomness byte (byte % 2) |\n| `get_tier_amount()` | tiers | create_match | Maps tier index (0-5) to lamport entry amount |\n| `transfer_lamports_to_pda()` | escrow | create_match, join_match | Deposits player funds into match PDA (system program CPI) |\n| `transfer_lamports_from_pda()` | escrow | claim_payout, timeout_cancel | Withdraws funds from match PDA (direct lamport manipulation) |\n| `calculate_net_payout()` | fees | claim_payout | Splits pool into (fee, net_payout); fee = pool × 300 bps |\n| `check_not_paused()` | pause | create_match | Checks game not paused; rejects if paused |\n| `transition()` | lifecycle | join_match, timeout_cancel | Validates phase transitions (returns error if invalid) |\n| `RoundPhase` enum | lifecycle | All instructions | Lifecycle states: Waiting, Locked, Settled, Refunded |\n| `is_expired()` | timeout | timeout_cancel | Checks if now >= deadline |\n| `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` | timeout | join_match | 120-second timeout constant |\n| `request_orao_randomness()` | vrf_orao | join_match | CPI into Orao VRF to request randomness; no-op in mock mode |\n| `read_orao_randomness()` | vrf_orao | claim_payout, timeout_cancel | Reads 32-byte randomness from Orao account; errors if unfulfilled |\n| `is_fulfilled()` | vrf_orao | timeout_cancel | Checks if randomness is non-zero (fulfilled) |\n| `update_player_profile_cpi()` | cpi | claim_payout | CPI to platform program to update player stats (wager, won, is_winner) |\n\n---\n\n### KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n\n1. **PDA Derivation**: All match PDAs use `[b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]`, enforcing one active match per creator. Config is singleton at `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`.\n\n2. **Phase State Machine**: Matches flow through phases: `Waiting` → `Locked` → (`Settled` or `Refunded`). Only `claim_payout` and `timeout_cancel` handle exits from `Locked`; `LOCKED → SETTLED` is not in the shared `transition()` function—`claim_payout` sets it directly after reading VRF.\n\n3. **VRF Workflow**: `join_match` requests Orao randomness and stores vrf_request_key. `claim_payout` reads the fulfilled randomness and settles. `timeout_cancel` refunds if deadline elapses and VRF is still unfulfilled (not read = unfulfilled).\n\n4. **Escrow Pattern**: Entry amounts are held in match PDA. On settlement, winner and treasury receive transfers via `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`. On timeout refund, both players receive transfers. Account closure refunds rent to creator.\n\n5. **Fee Calculation**: Fixed 300 bps (3%) total fee split: 200 bps revenue + 70 bps rakeback + 30 bps chest. Calculated once in `claim_payout` via `calculate_net_payout()`.\n\n6. **Profile Sync**: `claim_payout` CPIs into platform program to update both players' profile stats (games played, wins, total wagered, total won). CPI is silently skipped if profile doesn't exist (empty account guard).\n\n7. **Admin Authority**: `force_close` allows admin to emergency-close corrupted match accounts without deserializing; drains lamports and zeros data."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4b66679d061a43f9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57904\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 91120</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"17fa3561-dab0-4039-8766-dc12be800ed4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly inventory the coinflip program at `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/`. For each instruction file, list:\n1. All account structs and their fields/constraints\n2. Handler function logic (what it does step by step)\n3. Events emitted\n4. Error conditions checked\n5. Which shared crate functions are called\n\nAlso check state.rs for all structs/enums/events. Give me exact file:line references.","agentId":"a4b66679d061a43f9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! N