ed)\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 40-88)\n1. **Lines 44-47**: Require phase == Locked\n2. **Lines 50-55**: Validate creator and opponent accounts match stored keys via `require_keys_eq!` macro\n3. **Lines 57-62**: Check that resolve_deadline has expired via `is_expired(resolve_deadline, now)`\n4. **Lines 67-70**: Check that VRF randomness is NOT fulfilled:\n   - Attempt to read randomness via `read_orao_randomness()`\n   - If fulfilled and non-zero, reject with `InvalidPhase` (must use claim_payout instead)\n   - If not fulfilled or read fails, proceed with timeout refund\n5. **Line 72**: Get entry_amount from match\n6. **Lines 75-77**: Refund both players their entry amounts via `transfer_lamports_from_pda()` twice\n7. **Lines 80-82**: Transition phase to Refunded via `lifecycle::transition()` and update match state\n8. **Line 84**: Account closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint; remaining lamports (rent) returned to creator\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 46**: `InvalidPhase` — phase must be Locked\n- **Lines 50-55**: `require_keys_eq!` (Anchor macro) — creator and opponent keys must match stored values\n- **Line 61**: `LockTimeoutNotElapsed` — resolve_deadline must have elapsed (now >= deadline)\n- **Line 70**: `InvalidPhase` (reused) — VRF must NOT be fulfilled (if fulfilled, use claim_payout instead)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\n- **`rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda`** (line 2 import, lines 76-77 calls) — Refunds both players' entry amounts\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::transition`** (line 3 import, line 80 call) — Validates Locked → Refunded transition\n- **`rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase`** (line 3 import) — Enum\n- **`rng_shared::timeout::is_expired`** (line 4 import, line 60 call) — Returns true if now >= resolve_deadline\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled`** (line 5 import, line 68 call) — Returns true if randomness is non-zero (fulfilled)\n- **`rng_shared::vrf_orao::read_orao_randomness`** (line 5 import, line 67 call) — Reads randomness from Orao account; errors if not fulfilled\n\n---\n\n### INSTRUCTION: FORCE_CLOSE\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/force_close.rs`\n\n#### Account Struct (Lines 8-28)\n```rust\npub struct ForceClose<'info> {\n    pub authority: Signer<'info>,  // Line 11: Config authority (admin)\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n        has_one = authority,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,  // Line 19: Config PDA; validates authority via has_one\n\n    /// CHECK: The match account to close. Not deserialized — may have old layout.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub match_account: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 23: Match account to close (may be corrupted/undeserializable)\n\n    /// CHECK: Receives the lamports. Should be the match creator or admin.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub recipient: AccountInfo<'info>,  // Line 27: Recipient for drained lamports\n}\n```\n\n#### Handler Logic (Lines 30-45)\n1. **Line 34**: Verify match_account is owned by this program (coinflip program ID)\n2. **Line 37**: Get lamports balance from match_account\n3. **Line 38**: Drain all lamports from match_account to recipient\n4. **Line 42**: Zero the match_account's data to effectively close it\n\n#### Events Emitted\nNone\n\n#### Error Conditions Checked\n- **Line 34**: `require_keys_eq!` — match_account.owner must be coinflip program ID (crate::ID)\n\n#### Shared Crate Functions Called\nNone (admin utility; no shared functions)\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE: SHARED CRATE FUNCTION USAGE\n\n| Shared Function | Module | Instructions Using It | Purpose |\n|-----------------|--------|----------------------|---------|\n| `is_valid_side()` | constants | create_match | Validates side ∈ {0, 1} |\n| `from_randomness()` | constants | claim_payout | Derives coin side from randomness byte (byte % 2) |\n| `get_tier_amount()` | tiers | create_match | Maps tier index (0-5) to lamport entry amount |\n| `transfer_lamports_to_pda()` | escrow | create_match, join_match | Deposits player funds into match PDA (system program CPI) |\n| `transfer_lamports_from_pda()` | escrow | claim_payout, timeout_cancel | Withdraws funds from match PDA (direct lamport manipulation) |\n| `calculate_net_payout()` | fees | claim_payout | Splits pool into (fee, net_payout); fee = pool × 300 bps |\n| `check_not_paused()` | pause | create_match | Checks game not paused; rejects if paused |\n| `transition()` | lifecycle | join_match, timeout_cancel | Validates phase transitions (returns error if invalid) |\n| `RoundPhase` enum | lifecycle | All instructions | Lifecycle states: Waiting, Locked, Settled, Refunded |\n| `is_expired()` | timeout | timeout_cancel | Checks if now >= deadline |\n| `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` | timeout | join_match | 120-second timeout constant |\n| `request_orao_randomness()` | vrf_orao | join_match | CPI into Orao VRF to request randomness; no-op in mock mode |\n| `read_orao_randomness()` | vrf_orao | claim_payout, timeout_cancel | Reads 32-byte randomness from Orao account; errors if unfulfilled |\n| `is_fulfilled()` | vrf_orao | timeout_cancel | Checks if randomness is non-zero (fulfilled) |\n| `update_player_profile_cpi()` | cpi | claim_payout | CPI to platform program to update player stats (wager, won, is_winner) |\n\n---\n\n### KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n\n1. **PDA Derivation**: All match PDAs use `[b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]`, enforcing one active match per creator. Config is singleton at `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`.\n\n2. **Phase State Machine**: Matches flow through phases: `Waiting` → `Locked` → (`Settled` or `Refunded`). Only `claim_payout` and `timeout_cancel` handle exits from `Locked`; `LOCKED → SETTLED` is not in the shared `transition()` function—`claim_payout` sets it directly after reading VRF.\n\n3. **VRF Workflow**: `join_match` requests Orao randomness and stores vrf_request_key. `claim_payout` reads the fulfilled randomness and settles. `timeout_cancel` refunds if deadline elapses and VRF is still unfulfilled (not read = unfulfilled).\n\n4. **Escrow Pattern**: Entry amounts are held in match PDA. On settlement, winner and treasury receive transfers via `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`. On timeout refund, both players receive transfers. Account closure refunds rent to creator.\n\n5. **Fee Calculation**: Fixed 300 bps (3%) total fee split: 200 bps revenue + 70 bps rakeback + 30 bps chest. Calculated once in `claim_payout` via `calculate_net_payout()`.\n\n6. **Profile Sync**: `claim_payout` CPIs into platform program to update both players' profile stats (games played, wins, total wagered, total won). CPI is silently skipped if profile doesn't exist (empty account guard).\n\n7. **Admin Authority**: `force_close` allows admin to emergency-close corrupted match accounts without deserializing; drains lamports and zeros data."}],"totalDurationMs":91120,"totalTokens":57904,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1463,"cache_read_input_tokens":48416,"output_tokens":8022,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1463,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
