{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015hGzwbaBjpQGN99D5RrLJw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Gap Analysis — 004 Shared Infrastructure\n     2→\n     3→**Date**: 2026-02-25\n     4→**Spec Status**: Done (17 iterations)\n     5→**Auditor**: Automated gap-analysis (post-completion)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Codebase Inventory\n    10→\n    11→### Shared Crate (`solana/shared/src/`)\n    12→\n    13→| Module | File | Public API | Tests |\n    14→|--------|------|------------|-------|\n    15→| Lifecycle | `lifecycle.rs` | `RoundPhase` enum (6 variants), `RoundTimestamps` struct, `transition()`, `LifecycleError` | 3 unit tests |\n    16→| Timeout | `timeout.rs` | `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`, `is_expired()`, `enforce_not_expired()`, `TimeoutError` | 6 unit tests |\n    17→| Commit-Reveal | `commit_reveal.rs` | `store_commitment()`, `verify_reveal()`, `CommitRevealError` | 3 unit tests |\n    18→| Fees | `fees.rs` | `MAX_FEE_BPS`, `TOTAL_FEE_BPS`, `REVENUE_BPS`, `RAKEBACK_BPS`, `CHEST_BPS`, `calculate_fee()`, `calculate_net_payout()`, `split_fee()` | 4 unit tests |\n    19→| Pause | `pause.rs` | `check_not_paused()`, `PauseError` (2 variants) | 4 unit tests |\n    20→| Escrow | `escrow.rs` | `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`, `transfer_lamports_to_pda()`, `EscrowError` | doc-tests (ignored, runtime needed) |\n    21→| CPI | `cpi.rs` | `update_player_profile_cpi()` | doc-test (ignored, runtime needed) |\n    22→| VRF Orao | `vrf_orao.rs` | `VrfAuditFields`, `is_fulfilled()`, `request_orao_randomness()`, `read_orao_randomness()`, `VrfError` | 5 unit tests |\n    23→| Constants | `constants.rs` | `SIDE_HEADS`, `SIDE_TAILS`, `from_randomness()`, `is_valid_side()`, phase constants (legacy) | existing tests |\n    24→| Tiers | `tiers.rs` | `TIER_AMOUNTS`, `get_tier_amount()`, `TierError` | existing tests |\n    25→\n    26→**Total shared crate tests**: 27 unit tests + 3 ignored doc-tests.\n    27→**Features**: `mock-vrf` (gates Orao CPI vs. raw-byte test mode).\n    28→\n    29→### Coinflip Program (`solana/programs/coinflip/src/`)\n    30→\n    31→| Instruction | File | Shared Modules Used |\n    32→|-------------|------|---------------------|\n    33→| `initialize_config` | `initialize_config.rs` | — |\n    34→| `create_match` | `create_match.rs` | `pause`, `escrow`, `lifecycle`, `tiers`, `constants` |\n    35→| `join_match` | `join_match.rs` | `escrow`, `lifecycle`, `vrf_orao`, `timeout` |\n    36→| `claim_payout` | `claim_payout.rs` | `vrf_orao`, `constants`, `fees`, `escrow`, `cpi`, `lifecycle` |\n    37→| `cancel_match` | `cancel_match.rs` | `lifecycle` |\n    38→| `timeout_cancel` | `timeout_cancel.rs` | `timeout`, `vrf_orao`, `escrow`, `lifecycle` |\n    39→| `force_close` | `force_close.rs` | — (admin emergency) |\n    40→\n    41→**State**: `CoinflipMatch` (uses `RoundPhase`), `CoinflipConfig` (has `paused`), `MatchSettled` event.\n    42→**Dependencies**: `orao-solana-vrf` (CPI), `rng-shared`, `platform` (CPI). `ephemeral-vrf-sdk` removed.\n    43→**Features**: `mock-vrf` (default for test builds).\n    44→\n    45→### Coinflip Tests (`solana/tests/coinflip.ts`)\n    46→\n    47→28 bankrun tests across 7 groups: initialize_config (1), create_match (4), join_match (3), claim_payout (9), cancel_match (3), timeout_cancel (3), full lifecycle (3).\n    48→\n    49→### Frontend (`apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n    50→\n    51→Instruction builders: `buildCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`, `buildCancelMatchTx`, `buildTimeoutCancelTx`. Orao VRF PDAs derived correctly. Account queries: `fetchAllOpenMatches` (Waiting only), `fetchMatchByCreator`, `fetchMatch`.\n    52→\n    53→---\n    54→\n    55→## FR Audit\n    56→\n    57→### FR-1: Shared Crate — Escrow Helpers (Claim-Based Payout)\n    58→\n    59→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    60→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    61→| 1 | `deposit_to_escrow(from, round_pda, amount)` transfers SOL via system program CPI | **SATISFIED** | `escrow.rs:53` — `transfer_lamports_to_pda(from, pda, amount, system_program_info)`. Name differs but function is equivalent. Used in `create_match.rs:46-51` and `join_match.rs:70-75`. |\n    62→| 2 | `claim_payout` reads VRF result at claim time, derives winner, transfers payout | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:104` reads Orao randomness, `:107-112` derives winner, `:115-126` transfers payout+fee. |\n    63→| 3 | Either participant can trigger claim — payout goes to derived winner | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:79-83` allows creator or opponent. `:108-112` derives winner from VRF. Test: \"either player can trigger claim\". |\n    64→| 4 | Claim is idempotent — double-claim returns error | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:76` checks `!claimed`. PDA closed after claim (`:20`). Test: \"rejects double claim (account closed)\". |\n    65→| 5 | Claim emits Anchor event with VRF randomness, winner, payout amounts | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:156-163` emits `MatchSettled` with all required fields. `state.rs:55-63` defines event. |\n    66→| 6 | `refund(round_pda, caller)` — each depositor calls individually after timeout | **SATISFIED** | `timeout_cancel.rs:74-77` refunds both players atomically via `transfer_lamports_from_pda`. Design variance: single permissionless call vs. per-depositor. Functionally equivalent. |\n    67→| 7 | `close_round(round_pda, rent_recipient)` closes PDA and returns rent | **SATISFIED** | Handled by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint on `claim_payout.rs:20`, `cancel_match.rs:17`, `timeout_cancel.rs:29`. |\n    68→| 8 | No escrow function touches fee math | **SATISFIED** | `escrow.rs` contains only lamport transfer functions. Fee calculation is in `fees.rs`, called separately in `claim_payout.rs:116`. |\n    69→| 9 | Claimable games query: getProgramAccounts filter by player + phase + claimed | **GAP** | Frontend `chain.ts` only has `fetchAllOpenMatches` (Waiting phase, line 167). No \"claimable games per user\" query exists. No `getProgramAccounts` filter by player pubkey + LOCKED phase + claimed==false. No \"unresolved games\" list in the UI. |\n    70→\n    71→### FR-2: Commit-Reveal Verifier\n    72→\n    73→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    74→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    75→| 1 | `store_commitment(round_pda, hash)` stores SHA256 in round PDA | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:11` — `store_commitment(commitment: &mut [u8; 32], hash: [u8; 32])`. Takes mutable reference (better API for shared helper). |\n    76→| 2 | `verify_reveal(round_pda, server_seed)` checks SHA256 match | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:16` — `verify_reveal(commitment: &[u8; 32], server_seed: &[u8]) -> Result<()>`. |\n    77→| 3 | Verification failure returns typed error | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:5-8` — `CommitRevealError::CommitmentMismatch`. |\n    78→| 4 | On verification failure, round transitions to REFUNDED | **DEFERRED** | Requires a commit-reveal game consumer (crash, chart the course). Module provides the primitive; transition-to-REFUNDED logic belongs in the consuming game's handler. (002-crash is Draft status.) |\n    79→| 5 | No third-party dependency — uses solana_program::hash::hashv or equivalent | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:2` — uses `solana_sha256_hasher::hashv` (Solana SDK v2 subcrate, not third-party). |\n    80→| 6 | Module is independently testable (unit tests with known hash pairs) | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:26-56` — 3 tests: known pair passes, tampered seed fails, empty seed fails. |\n    81→\n    82→### FR-3: Fee Distribution\n    83→\n    84→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    85→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    86→| 1 | `calculate_fee(pool) -> (fee, net_payout)` | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:25` — `calculate_net_payout(pool: u64) -> (u64, u64)` returns `(fee, net_payout)`. |\n    87→| 2 | Fee = 300 bps (3%) hardcoded | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:8` — `TOTAL_FEE_BPS: u16 = 300`. Used in `calculate_fee` at `:18-20`. |\n    88→| 3 | `transfer_fee(round_pda, treasury_pda, fee_amount)` sends fee to treasury | **SATISFIED** | No dedicated function; `escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda` used in `claim_payout.rs:126`. Generic escrow helper serves this purpose. |\n    89→| 4 | Integer math only — no floats | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:19` — `u128` intermediate for multiplication/division. All integer operations. |\n    90→| 5 | Rounding favors the player (fee rounds down) | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:19` — integer division truncates (rounds down). Test at `:68-70` confirms 1 lamport → fee=0, net=1. |\n    91→| 6 | `MAX_FEE_BPS = 1000` compile-time safety cap | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:2` — `MAX_FEE_BPS: u16 = 1000`. Compile-time assertion at `:14`. |\n    92→| 7 | Fee split (200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest) tracked, single treasury transfer for V1 | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:9-11` — constants match spec. `split_fee()` at `:31-36`. `claim_payout.rs:126` does single treasury transfer. |\n    93→\n    94→### FR-4: VRF Provider Integration (Orao)\n    95→\n    96→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    97→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    98→| 1 | Orao selection documented in DECISIONS.md | **SATISFIED** | `DECISIONS.md` — \"Decision: VRF Provider = Orao (MagicBlock dropped)\", dated 2026-02-25, Status: Locked. |\n    99→| 2 | Shared helper module (vrf_orao.rs) — request, read, fulfillment check | **SATISFIED** | `vrf_orao.rs` — `request_orao_randomness` (`:31`), `read_orao_randomness` (`:57`), `is_fulfilled` (`:21`). |\n   100→| 3 | VRF request embedded in game instruction (not separate) | **SATISFIED** | `join_match.rs:78-87` — Orao CPI embedded in `join_match`. |\n   101→| 4 | claim_payout reads Orao randomness, derives outcome, settles | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:104` reads, `:107-112` derives, `:115-126` settles. |\n   102→| 5 | Claim emits event with randomness + derived outcome | **SATISFIED**