D invalid. |\n   116→| 3 | Timeout invariant: resolve_deadline set, VRF-fulfilled check before timeout | **SATISFIED** | `join_match.rs` sets `resolve_deadline`. `timeout_cancel.rs:58-70` checks deadline + VRF NOT fulfilled. Test: \"rejects timeout when VRF IS fulfilled\". |\n   117→| 4 | Pause invariant: global + per-game pause, existing rounds can settle | **SATISFIED** | `pause.rs:13` — `check_not_paused(global, game)`. `create_match.rs:39` checks pause. `claim_payout.rs` and `timeout_cancel.rs` do NOT check pause (existing rounds can settle/refund). `CoinflipConfig.paused` at `state.rs:14`. |\n   118→| 5 | Refund invariant: refundable if deadline passed + resolution source not fulfilled | **SATISFIED** | `timeout_cancel.rs:67-70` — checks VRF NOT fulfilled. If fulfilled, refund rejected (must claim). Prevents claim-vs-refund racing. |\n   119→| 6 | Phase transitions emit Anchor events for frontend consumption | **GAP** | Only settlement emits an event (`MatchSettled` in `claim_payout.rs:156`). Create (Waiting), join (Locked), cancel (Refunded), timeout (Refunded) transitions do NOT emit Anchor events. |\n   120→| 7 | Timestamp tracking: created_at, locked_at, resolve_deadline, settled_at | **GAP** (partial) | `CoinflipMatch` has `created_at` (`:43`), `locked_at` (`:45`), `resolve_deadline` (`:47`) but NOT `settled_at`. Shared `RoundTimestamps` struct defines all 4 fields (`:16-21`), but CoinflipMatch uses inline fields and omits `settled_at`. Since PDA is closed after claim, `settled_at` would be unreadable on-chain — but could be useful in the emitted event or tx logs. |\n   121→\n   122→### FR-6: Platform CPI Helpers\n   123→\n   124→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n   125→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n   126→| 1 | `update_player_profile(program, profile_pda, game, wins, wager, won)` CPIs into platform | **SATISFIED** | `cpi.rs:41` — `update_player_profile_cpi(platform_program, profile, authority, signer_seeds, total_games_delta, wins_delta, total_wagered_delta, total_won_delta)`. |\n   127→| 2 | CPI conditional — skipped if profile PDA empty | **SATISFIED** | `cpi.rs:52-54` — `if profile.data_is_empty() { return Ok(()); }`. |\n   128→| 3 | Both players' profiles updated on settlement | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:133-153` — CPI for both creator and opponent. Tests: \"updates player profiles via CPI — creator wins\" and \"opponent wins\". |\n   129→| 4 | CPI helper generic for all game types (accepts game discriminator) | **GAP** (minor) | No game discriminator parameter. The CPI helper and platform program's `update_player_profile` instruction both lack a game type field. Profile stats are aggregated without per-game attribution. |\n   130→\n   131→---\n   132→\n   133→## Summary\n   134→\n   135→| Verdict | Count | Details |\n   136→|---------|-------|---------|\n   137→| **SATISFIED** | 35 | All core escrow, fee, lifecycle, VRF, commit-reveal, pause, and CPI functionality implemented and tested |\n   138→| **DEFERRED** | 1 | FR-2 AC-4 — commit-reveal failure→REFUNDED transition (requires crash or other commit-reveal game consumer; 002-crash is Draft) |\n   139→| **GAP** | 4 | See below |\n   140→\n   141→### Gaps\n   142→\n   143→| ID | FR | Criterion | Gap Description | Severity |\n   144→|----|----|-----------|-----------------|---------|\n   145→| G-1 | FR-1 AC-9 | Claimable games query | Frontend has no \"claimable/unresolved games per user\" query. `fetchAllOpenMatches` only returns Waiting phase. No `getProgramAccounts` filter by player + LOCKED + claimed==false. | Medium — UX feature, not safety-critical. Players can still claim via direct match lookup. |\n   146→| G-2 | FR-5 AC-6 | Phase transition events | Only `MatchSettled` event emitted (on claim). Create, join, cancel, and timeout transitions do not emit Anchor events. Frontend relies on account polling instead of event streams. | Low — functional but reduces event-driven frontend capability. Account polling works as fallback. |\n   147→| G-3 | FR-5 AC-7 | `settled_at` timestamp | `CoinflipMatch` lacks `settled_at` field. Shared `RoundTimestamps` defines it but coinflip uses inline fields and omits it. PDA is closed after claim so the field would be unreadable on-chain, but could be useful in emitted event data. | Low — `MatchSettled` event timestamp from the tx itself serves as proxy. |\n   148→| G-4 | FR-6 AC-4 | Game discriminator in CPI | CPI helper and platform `update_player_profile` lack a game type discriminator. Profile stats are aggregated without per-game attribution. | Low — V1 has one game (coinflip). Becomes relevant when Lord of the RNGs is added. |\n   149→\n   150→### Test Coverage Observations\n   151→\n   152→| Observation | Impact |\n   153→|-------------|--------|\n   154→| No bankrun test for pause blocking `create_match` | Low — pause logic is unit-tested in `pause.rs`. Integration test gap only. |\n   155→| No assertion on `MatchSettled` event emission in bankrun tests | Low — event is emitted (verified by code inspection). Missing test assertion, not missing functionality. |\n   156→\n   157→### Recommendation Disposition (Sorted)\n   158→\n   159→| Gap | Recommendation | Disposition | Target Spec/Checklist | Priority |\n   160→|-----|----------------|-------------|-----------------------|----------|\n   161→| G-1 | Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` for unresolved/claimable matches | **Accepted (planned)** | `docs/specs/001-coinflip/checklist.md` (frontend carry-forward) | Medium |\n   162→| G-2 | Add lifecycle transition events (`MatchCreated`, `MatchJoined`, `MatchCancelled`, `MatchTimedOut`) | **Accepted (planned)** | `docs/specs/003-platform-core/checklist.md` (observability carry-forward) | Low |\n   163→| G-3 | Add `settled_at` field to coinflip match account | **Deferred / No action for V1** | N/A (tx timestamp on `MatchSettled` event is sufficient while PDA closes) | Low |\n   164→| G-4 | Add game discriminator to profile CPI/update path | **Accepted (deferred to game #2)** | `docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/checklist.md` (implementation carry-forward) | Low |\n   165→\n   166→### Recommendation Notes\n   167→\n   168→1. **G-1 (Medium)**: Treat this as a frontend usability gap, not a protocol gap. Keep in Coinflip follow-up scope.\n   169→2. **G-2 (Low)**: Keep polling as the current compatibility path; add events when indexer/event-driven UX work is scheduled.\n   170→3. **G-3 (Low)**: No change for V1. If a persistent settlement timestamp is needed later, emit it in events/indexer records rather than reopening closed-PDA design.\n   171→4. **G-4 (Low)**: Implement before/with Lord of the RNGs so profile stats become per-game attributable from game #2 onward.\n   172→\n   173→---\n   174→\n   175→## Cross-References\n   176→\n   177→- FR-2 AC-4 deferred: 002-crash (Draft) will be the first commit-reveal consumer.\n   178→- FR-6 AC-4 gap: Relevant when 101-lord-of-the-rngs is implemented.\n   179→- G-1 (claimable games query): May belong to 003-platform-core (Draft) or 001-coinflip frontend scope.\n   180→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"1200afd8-8c63-4da9-bfdf-8b0170651adb","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/gap-analysis.md","content":"# Gap Analysis — 004 Shared Infrastructure\n\n**Date**: 2026-02-25\n**Spec Status**: Done (17 iterations)\n**Auditor**: Automated gap-analysis (post-completion)\n\n---\n\n## Codebase Inventory\n\n### Shared Crate (`solana/shared/src/`)\n\n| Module | File | Public API | Tests |\n|--------|------|------------|-------|\n| Lifecycle | `lifecycle.rs` | `RoundPhase` enum (6 variants), `RoundTimestamps` struct, `transition()`, `LifecycleError` | 3 unit tests |\n| Timeout | `timeout.rs` | `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`, `is_expired()`, `enforce_not_expired()`, `TimeoutError` | 6 unit tests |\n| Commit-Reveal | `commit_reveal.rs` | `store_commitment()`, `verify_reveal()`, `CommitRevealError` | 3 unit tests |\n| Fees | `fees.rs` | `MAX_FEE_BPS`, `TOTAL_FEE_BPS`, `REVENUE_BPS`, `RAKEBACK_BPS`, `CHEST_BPS`, `calculate_fee()`, `calculate_net_payout()`, `split_fee()` | 4 unit tests |\n| Pause | `pause.rs` | `check_not_paused()`, `PauseError` (2 variants) | 4 unit tests |\n| Escrow | `escrow.rs` | `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`, `transfer_lamports_to_pda()`, `EscrowError` | doc-tests (ignored, runtime needed) |\n| CPI | `cpi.rs` | `update_player_profile_cpi()` | doc-test (ignored, runtime needed) |\n| VRF Orao | `vrf_orao.rs` | `VrfAuditFields`, `is_fulfilled()`, `request_orao_randomness()`, `read_orao_randomness()`, `VrfError` | 5 unit tests |\n| Constants | `constants.rs` | `SIDE_HEADS`, `SIDE_TAILS`, `from_randomness()`, `is_valid_side()`, phase constants (legacy) | existing tests |\n| Tiers | `tiers.rs` | `TIER_AMOUNTS`, `get_tier_amount()`, `TierError` | existing tests |\n\n**Total shared crate tests**: 27 unit tests + 3 ignored doc-tests.\n**Features**: `mock-vrf` (gates Orao CPI vs. raw-byte test mode).\n\n### Coinflip Program (`solana/programs/coinflip/src/`)\n\n| Instruction | File | Shared Modules Used |\n|-------------|------|---------------------|\n| `initialize_config` | `initialize_config.rs` | — |\n| `create_match` | `create_match.rs` | `pause`, `escrow`, `lifecycle`, `tiers`, `constants` |\n| `join_match` | `join_match.rs` | `escrow`, `lifecycle`, `vrf_orao`, `timeout` |\n| `claim_payout` | `claim_payout.rs` | `vrf_orao`, `constants`, `fees`, `escrow`, `cpi`, `lifecycle` |\n| `cancel_match` | `cancel_match.rs` | `lifecycle` |\n| `timeout_cancel` | `timeout_cancel.rs` | `timeout`, `vrf_orao`, `escrow`, `lifecycle` |\n| `force_close` | `force_close.rs` | — (admin emergency) |\n\n**State**: `CoinflipMatch` (uses `RoundPhase`), `CoinflipConfig` (has `paused`), `MatchSettled` event.\n**Dependencies**: `orao-solana-vrf` (CPI), `rng-shared`, `platform` (CPI). `ephemeral-vrf-sdk` removed.\n**Features**: `mock-vrf` (default for test builds).\n\n### Coinflip Tests (`solana/tests/coinflip.ts`)\n\n28 bankrun tests across 7 groups: initialize_config (1), create_match (4), join_match (3), claim_payout (9), cancel_match (3), timeout_cancel (3), full lifecycle (3).\n\n### Frontend (`apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n\nInstruction builders: `buildCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`, `buildCancelMatchTx`, `buildTimeoutCancelTx`. Orao VRF PDAs derived correctly. Account queries: `fetchAllOpenMatches` (Waiting only), `fetchMatchByCreator`, `fetchMatch`.\n\n---\n\n## FR Audit\n\n### FR-1: Shared Crate — Escrow Helpers (Claim-Based Payout)\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `deposit_to_escrow(from, round_pda, amount)` transfers SOL via system program CPI | **SATISFIED** | `escrow.rs:53` — `transfer_lamports_to_pda(from, pda, amount, system_program_info)`. Name differs but function is equivalent. Used in `create_match.rs:46-51` and `join_match.rs:70-75`. |\n| 2 | `claim_payout` reads VRF result at claim time, derives winner, transfers payout | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:104` reads Orao randomness, `:107-112` derives winner, `:115-126` transfers payout+fee. |\n| 3 | Either participant can trigger claim — payout goes to derived winner | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:79-83` allows creator or opponent. `:108-112` derives winner from VRF. Test: \"either player can trigger claim\". |\n| 4 | Claim is idempotent — double-claim returns error | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:76` checks `!claimed`. PDA closed after claim (`:20`). Test: \"rejects double claim (account closed)\". |\n| 5 | Claim emits Anchor event with VRF randomness, winner, payout amounts | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:156-163` emits `MatchSettled` with all required fields. `state.rs:55-63` defines event. |\n| 6 | `refund(round_pda, caller)` — each depositor calls individually after timeout | **SATISFIED** | `timeout_cancel.rs:74-77` refunds both players atomically via `transfer_lamports_from_pda`. Design variance: single permissionless call vs. per-depositor. Functionally equivalent. |\n| 7 | `close_round(round_pda, rent_recipient)` closes PDA and returns rent | **SATISFIED** | Handled by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint on `claim_payout.rs:20`, `cancel_match.rs:17`, `timeout_cancel.rs:29`. |\n| 8 | No escrow function touches fee math | **SATISFIED** | `escrow.rs` contains only lamport transfer functions. Fee calculation is in `fees.rs`, called separately in `claim_payout.rs:116`. |\n| 9 | Claimable games query: getProgramAccounts filter by player + phase + claimed | **GAP** | Frontend `chain.ts` only has `fetchAllOpenMatches` (Waiting phase, line 167). No \"claimable games per user\" query exists. No `getProgramAccounts` filter by player pubkey + LOCKED phase + claimed==false. No \"unresolved games\" list in the UI. |\n\n### FR-2: Commit-Reveal Verifier\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `store_commitment(round_pda, hash)` stores SHA256 in round PDA | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:11` — `store_commitment(commitment: &mut [u8; 32], hash: [u8; 32])`. Takes mutable reference (better API for shared helper). |\n| 2 | `verify_reveal(round_pda, server_seed)` checks SHA256 match | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:16` — `verify_reveal(commitment: &[u8; 32], server_seed: &[u8]) -> Result<()>`. |\n| 3 | Verification failure returns typed error | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:5-8` — `CommitRevealError::CommitmentMismatch`. |\n| 4 | On verification failure, round transitions to REFUNDED | **DEFERRED** | Requires a commit-reveal game consumer (crash, chart the course). Module provides the primitive; transition-to-REFUNDED logic belongs in the consuming game's handler. (002-crash is Draft status.) |\n| 5 | No third-party dependency — uses solana_program::hash::hashv or equivalent | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:2` — uses `solana_sha256_hasher::hashv` (Solana SDK v2 subcrate, not third-party). |\n| 6 | Module is independently testable (unit tests with known hash pairs) | **SATISFIED** | `commit_reveal.rs:26-56` — 3 tests: known pair passes, tampered seed fails, empty seed fails. |\n\n### FR-3: Fee Distribution\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `calculate_fee(pool) -> (fee, net_payout)` | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:25` — `calculate_net_payout(pool: u64) -> (u64, u64)` returns `(fee, net_payout)`. |\n| 2 | Fee = 300 bps (3%) hardcoded | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:8` — `TOTAL_FEE_BPS: u16 = 300`. Used in `calculate_fee` at `:18-20`. |\n| 3 | `transfer_fee(round_pda, treasury_pda, fee_amount)` sends fee to treasury | **SATISFIED** | No dedicated function; `escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda` used in `claim_payout.rs:126`. Generic escrow helper serves this purpose. |\n| 4 | Integer math only — no floats | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:19` — `u128` intermediate for multiplication/division. All integer operations. |\n| 5 | Rounding favors the player (fee rounds down) | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:19` — integer division truncates (rounds down). Test at `:68-70` confirms 1 lamport → fee=0, net=1. |\n| 6 | `MAX_FEE_BPS = 1000` compile-time safety cap | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:2` — `MAX_FEE_BPS: u16 = 1000`. Compile-time assertion at `:14`. |\n| 7 | Fee split (200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest) tracked, single treasury transfer for V1 | **SATISFIED** | `fees.rs:9-11` — constants match spec. `split_fee()` at `:31-36`. `claim_payout.rs:126` does single treasury transfer. |\n\n### FR-4: VRF Provider Integration (Orao)\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | Orao selection documented in DECISIONS.md | **SATISFIED** | `DECISIONS.md` — \"Decision: VRF Provider = Orao (MagicBlock dropped)\", dated 2026-02-25, Status: Locked. |\n| 2 | Shared helper module (vrf_orao.rs) — request, read, fulfillment check | **SATISFIED** | `vrf_orao.rs` — `request_orao_randomness` (`:31`), `read_orao_randomness` (`:57`), `is_fulfilled` (`:21`). |\n| 3 | VRF request embedded in game instruction (not separate) | **SATISFIED** | `join_match.rs:78-87` — Orao CPI embedded in `join_match`. |\n| 4 | claim_payout reads Orao randomness, derives outcome, settles | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:104` reads, `:107-112` derives, `:115-126` settles. |\n| 5 | Claim emits event with randomness + derived outcome | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:156-163` — `MatchSettled` event with `randomness: [u8; 32]` and `winner`. |\n| 6 | Claim with unfulfilled randomness rejected with clear error | **SATISFIED** | `vrf_orao.rs:71/103` returns `VrfError::RandomnessNotFulfilled`. Test: \"rejects claim with unfulfilled randomness\". |\n| 7 | Outcome derivation deterministic, uses only on-chain/public inputs | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:107` — `from_randomness(randomness[0])` in `constants.rs:15` — `byte % 2`. Deterministic. |\n| 8 | Timeout path permissionless when VRF not fulfilled | **SATISFIED** | `timeout_cancel.rs:11-14` — any signer. `:58-70` checks deadline + VRF unfulfilled. Test: \"permissionless refund after deadline when VRF unfulfilled\". |\n| 9 | `mock-vrf` feature flag | **SATISFIED** | `shared/Cargo.toml` has `mock-vrf`. `vrf_orao.rs:80-91` (no-op request), `:96-105` (raw bytes read). Coinflip default features include `mock-vrf`. |\n| 10 | Reference implementation: Coinflip (001) | **SATISFIED** | Coinflip program fully rewritten using shared crate + Orao VRF. 28 bankrun tests pass. |\n| 11 | Drop all MagicBlock VRF references | **SATISFIED** | `grep -r \"MagicBlock\\|ephemeral.vrf\" sources/rng-utopia/solana/ sources/rng-utopia/CLAUDE.md` returns zero matches. Only historical mention in `docs/talk/composer.md` (archived architecture doc). |\n\n### FR-5: On-Chain Lifecycle State Machine\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `RoundPhase` enum: Waiting, Active, Locked, Resolving, Settled, Refunded | **SATISFIED** | `lifecycle.rs:5-12` — all 6 variants. Correct derives (AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Debug, InitSpace). |\n| 2 | `transition(current, target)` validates allowed transitions, rejects LOCKED→SETTLED | **SATISFIED** | `lifecycle.rs:39-58` — 9 allowed transitions. Test at `:88-89` confirms LOCKED→SETTLED invalid. |\n| 3 | Timeout invariant: resolve_deadline set, VRF-fulfilled check before timeout | **SATISFIED** | `join_match.rs` sets `resolve_deadline`. `timeout_cancel.rs:58-70` checks deadline + VRF NOT fulfilled. Test: \"rejects timeout when VRF IS fulfilled\". |\n| 4 | Pause invariant: global + per-game pause, existing rounds can settle | **SATISFIED** | `pause.rs:13` — `check_not_paused(global, game)`. `create_match.rs:39` checks pause. `claim_payout.rs` and `timeout_cancel.rs` do NOT check pause (existing rounds can settle/refund). `CoinflipConfig.paused` at `state.rs:14`. |\n| 5 | Refund invariant: refundable if deadline passed + resolution source not fulfilled | **SATISFIED** | `timeout_cancel.rs:67-70` — checks VRF NOT fulfilled. If fulfilled, refund rejected (must claim). Prevents claim-vs-refund racing. |\n| 6 | Phase transitions emit Anchor events for frontend consumption | **GAP** | Only settlement emits an event (`MatchSettled` in `claim_payout.rs:156`). Create (Waiting), join (Locked), cancel (Refunded), timeout (Refunded) transitions do NOT emit Anchor events. |\n| 7 | Timestamp tracking: created_at, locked_at, resolve_deadline, settled_at | **GAP** (partial) | `CoinflipMatch` has `created_at` (`:43`), `locked_at` (`:45`), `resolve_deadline` (`:47`) but NOT `settled_at`. Shared `RoundTimestamps` struct defines all 4 fields (`:16-21`), but CoinflipMatch uses inline fields and omits `settled_at`. Since PDA is closed after claim, `settled_at` would be unreadable on-chain — but could be useful in the emitted event or tx logs. |\n\n### FR-6: Platform CPI Helpers\n\n| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `update_player_profile(program, profile_pda, game, wins, wager, won)` CPIs into platform | **SATISFIED** | `cpi.rs:41` — `update_player_profile_cpi(platform_program, profile, authority, signer_seeds, total_games_delta, wins_delta, total_wagered_delta, total_won_delta)`. |\n| 2 | CPI conditional — skipped if profile PDA empty | **SATISFIED** | `cpi.rs:52-54` — `if profile.data_is_empty() { return Ok(()); }`. |\n| 3 | Both players' profiles updated on settlement | **SATISFIED** | `claim_payout.rs:133-153` — CPI for both creator and opponent. Tests: \"updates player profiles via CPI — creator wins\" and \"opponent wins\". |\n| 4 | CPI helper generic for all game types (accepts game discriminator) | **GAP** (minor) | No game discriminator parameter. The CPI helper and platform program's `update_player_profile` instruction both lack a game type field. Profile stats are aggregated without per-game attribution. |\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Verdict | Count | Details |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| **SATISFIED** | 35 | All core escrow, fee, lifecycle, VRF, commit-reveal, pause, and CPI functionality implemented and tested |\n| **DEFERRED** | 1 | FR-2 AC-4 — commit-reveal failure→REFUNDED transition (requires crash or other commit-reveal game consumer; 002-crash is Draft) |\n| **GAP** | 4 | See below |\n\n### Gaps\n\n| ID | FR | Criterion | Gap Description | Severity |\n|----|----|-----------|-----------------|---------|\n| G-1 | FR-1 AC-9 | Claimable games query | Frontend has no \"claimable/unresolved games per user\" query. `fetchAllOpenMatches` only returns Waiting phase. No `getProgramAccounts` filter by player + LOCKED + claimed==false. | Medium — UX feature, not safety-critical. Players can still claim via direct match lookup. |\n| G-2 | FR-5 AC-6 | Phase transition events | Only `MatchSettled` event emitted (on claim). Create, join, cancel, and timeout transitions do not emit Anchor events. Frontend relies on account polling instead of event streams. | Low — functional but reduces event-driven frontend capability. Account polling works as fallback. |\n| G-3 | FR-5 AC-7 | `settled_at` timestamp | `CoinflipMatch` lacks `settled_at` field. Shared `RoundTimestamps` defines it but coinflip uses inline fields and omits it. PDA is closed after claim so the field would be unreadable on-chain, but could be useful in emitted event data. | Low — `MatchSettled` event timestamp from the tx itself serves as proxy. |\n| G-4 | FR-6 AC-4 | Game discriminator in CPI | CPI helper and platform `update_player_profile` lack a game type discriminator. Profile stats are aggregated without per-game attribution. | Low — V1 has one game (coinflip). Becomes relevant when Lord of the RNGs is added. |\n\n### Test Coverage Observations\n\n| Observation | Impact |\n|-------------|--------|\n| No bankrun test for pause blocking `create_match` | Low — pause logic is unit-tested in `pause.rs`. Integration test gap only. |\n| No assertion on `MatchSettled` event emission in bankrun tests | Low — event is emitted (verified by code inspection). Missing test assertion, not missing functionality. |\n\n### Recommendation Disposition (Sorted)\n\n| Gap | Recommendation | Disposition | Target Spec/Checklist | Priority |\n|-----|----------------|-------------|-----------------------|----------|\n| G-1 | Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` for unresolved/claimable matches | **Accepted (planned)** | `docs/specs/001-coinflip/checklist.md` (frontend carry-forward) | Medium |\n| G-2 | Add lifecycle transition events (`MatchCreated`, `MatchJoined`, `MatchCancelled`, `MatchTimedOut`) | **Accepted (planned)** | `docs/specs/003-platform-core/checklist.md` (observability carry-forward) | Low |\n| G-3 | Add `settled_at` field to coinflip match account | **Deferred / No action for V1** | N/A (tx timestamp on `MatchSettled` event is sufficient while PDA closes) | Low |\n| G-4 | Add game discriminator to profile CPI/update path | **Accepted (deferred to game #2)** | `docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/checklist.md` (implementation carry-forward) | Low |\n\n### Recommendation Notes\n\n1. **G-1 (Medium)**: Treat this as a frontend usability gap, not a protocol gap. Keep in Coinflip follow-up scope.\n2. **G-2 (Low)**: Keep polling as the current compatibility path; add events when indexer/event-driven UX work is scheduled.\n3. **G-3 (Low)**: No change for V1. If a persistent settlement timestamp is needed later, emit it in events/indexer records rather than reopening closed-PDA design.\n4. **G-4 (Low)**: Implement before/with Lord of the RNGs so profile stats become per-game attributable from game #2 onward.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-References\n\n- FR-2 AC-4 deferred: 002-crash (Draft) will be the first commit-reveal consumer.\n- FR-6 AC-4 gap: Relevant when 101-lord-of-the-rngs is implemented.\n- G-1 (claimable games query): May belong to 003-platform-core (Draft) or 001-coinflip frontend scope.\n","numLines":180,"startLine":1,"totalLines":180}}}
