{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015ShR4DAECs5c442tJgmTLz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification Quality Checklist: 001 Coinflip\n     2→\n     3→**Purpose**: Validate specification completeness and quality before implementation\n     4→**Created**: 2026-02-12\n     5→**Refined**: 2026-02-17\n     6→**Spec**: [spec.md](spec.md)\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## Content Quality\n    11→\n    12→- [x] No implementation details (languages, frameworks, APIs)\n    13→- [x] Focused on user value and business needs\n    14→- [x] Written for non-technical stakeholders\n    15→- [x] All mandatory sections completed\n    16→\n    17→## Requirement Completeness\n    18→\n    19→- [x] No [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] markers remain\n    20→- [x] Requirements are testable and unambiguous\n    21→- [x] Success criteria are measurable\n    22→- [x] Success criteria are technology-agnostic\n    23→- [x] Acceptance criteria are defined\n    24→- [x] Edge cases are identified\n    25→- [x] Scope is clearly bounded\n    26→- [x] Dependencies and assumptions identified\n    27→\n    28→## Feature Readiness\n    29→\n    30→- [x] All functional requirements have clear acceptance criteria\n    31→- [x] User scenarios cover primary flows\n    32→- [x] Feature meets measurable outcomes defined in Success Criteria\n    33→- [x] No implementation details leak into specification\n    34→\n    35→---\n    36→\n    37→## Open Items\n    38→\n    39→| # | Item | Category | Blocking? | Status |\n    40→|---|------|----------|-----------|--------|\n    41→| 1 | Contract files not identified (frontend mocks, on-chain interfaces) | Contract | Yes | **Resolved** — all contract files identified in spec §Contract Files |\n    42→| 2 | Platform fee inconsistency: game docs use 3%, PLATFORM.md says 2.0-2.2% | Assumption | Yes | **Resolved** — FOUNDATIONS.md §8 confirms 3% (300 bps). PLATFORM.md is outdated, not authoritative. |\n    43→| 3 | One-active-match-per-player limit not specified in source docs | FR-1 | No | **Resolved** — enforced by PDA seeds `[b\"match\", creator]` (one match per creator) |\n    44→| 4 | Estimated wait time data source undefined | FR-6 | No | **Deferred** — post-MVP polish, noted in FR-6 AC |\n    45→| 5 | Edge case: creator cancels before opponent joins | Edge Case | No | **Resolved** — cancel_match instruction handles this (WAITING phase only) |\n    46→| 6 | Edge case: timeout on unjoined matches (expiry policy) | Edge Case | No | **Deferred** — no auto-expiry in V1, creator must cancel manually |\n    47→| 7 | Edge case: wallet disconnect during flip/settlement | Edge Case | No | **In scope** — frontend error handling checklist item covers this |\n    48→| 8 | Edge case: VRF request timeout or failure handling | Edge Case | No | **Deferred** — mock oracle in V1, MagicBlock VRF integration deferred |\n    49→\n    50→## Refinement Decisions (2026-02-17)\n    51→\n    52→| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n    53→|----------|--------|-----------|\n    54→| Tier amounts | Frontend/spec values canonical | Iron→Diamond, [0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0] SOL. On-chain shared crate updated to match. |\n    55→| Coin side discriminants | 0/1 (on-chain canonical) | heads=0, tails=1. Game-engine updated to match. |\n    56→| VRF approach | Mock oracle for V1 | Test keypair signs resolve_match. MagicBlock deferred. |\n    57→| Platform program | Included in spec | CPI for player profile updates on settlement. |\n    58→| Spec scope | On-chain + engine + frontend | Audio, fairness UI, animation polish, Playwright tests deferred. |\n    59→| PDA structure | Rewrite game-engine | Delete old BOLT ECS PDAs, use simple creator-based PDAs matching on-chain. |\n    60→\n    61→## Refinement Carry-Forward (Pivot)\n    62→\n    63→- [ ] Lock Coinflip fairness proof contract fields and verification path for selected VRF provider.\n    64→- [ ] Confirm determinism boundary: contract derives final outcome from verifiable on-chain/public inputs only.\n    65→- [ ] Add explicit timeout/refund acceptance checks aligned to shared lifecycle invariants.\n    66→- [ ] Reconfirm idempotency/replay protection requirements for join, resolve, and payout/claim paths.\n    67→- [ ] Add failure-mode acceptance checks for VRF callback delay/failure and pause-state behavior.\n    68→\n    69→## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n    70→\n    71→- [ ] Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` in coinflip `chain.ts` for claimable/unresolved matches.\n    72→- [ ] Ensure claimable query covers player as creator OR opponent, `claimed == false`, and non-terminal phases that can still be claimed.\n    73→- [ ] Expose claimable matches in frontend UX (for example, \"Pending Claims\" or equivalent unresolved matches list).\n    74→\n    75→## Notes\n    76→\n    77→- Source material (COINFLIP.md) is well-specified for core flows\n    78→- All blocking items resolved during /refine interview (2026-02-17)\n    79→- 12 granular checklist items in spec, ordered by dependency\n    80→- 8 functional requirements extracted, all with acceptance criteria\n    81→- Validation plan covers all critical paths\n    82→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"4eb23f7c-59d8-4e5c-82ee-6a9156358877","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/checklist.md","content":"# Specification Quality Checklist: 001 Coinflip\n\n**Purpose**: Validate specification completeness and quality before implementation\n**Created**: 2026-02-12\n**Refined**: 2026-02-17\n**Spec**: [spec.md](spec.md)\n\n---\n\n## Content Quality\n\n- [x] No implementation details (languages, frameworks, APIs)\n- [x] Focused on user value and business needs\n- [x] Written for non-technical stakeholders\n- [x] All mandatory sections completed\n\n## Requirement Completeness\n\n- [x] No [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] markers remain\n- [x] Requirements are testable and unambiguous\n- [x] Success criteria are measurable\n- [x] Success criteria are technology-agnostic\n- [x] Acceptance criteria are defined\n- [x] Edge cases are identified\n- [x] Scope is clearly bounded\n- [x] Dependencies and assumptions identified\n\n## Feature Readiness\n\n- [x] All functional requirements have clear acceptance criteria\n- [x] User scenarios cover primary flows\n- [x] Feature meets measurable outcomes defined in Success Criteria\n- [x] No implementation details leak into specification\n\n---\n\n## Open Items\n\n| # | Item | Category | Blocking? | Status |\n|---|------|----------|-----------|--------|\n| 1 | Contract files not identified (frontend mocks, on-chain interfaces) | Contract | Yes | **Resolved** — all contract files identified in spec §Contract Files |\n| 2 | Platform fee inconsistency: game docs use 3%, PLATFORM.md says 2.0-2.2% | Assumption | Yes | **Resolved** — FOUNDATIONS.md §8 confirms 3% (300 bps). PLATFORM.md is outdated, not authoritative. |\n| 3 | One-active-match-per-player limit not specified in source docs | FR-1 | No | **Resolved** — enforced by PDA seeds `[b\"match\", creator]` (one match per creator) |\n| 4 | Estimated wait time data source undefined | FR-6 | No | **Deferred** — post-MVP polish, noted in FR-6 AC |\n| 5 | Edge case: creator cancels before opponent joins | Edge Case | No | **Resolved** — cancel_match instruction handles this (WAITING phase only) |\n| 6 | Edge case: timeout on unjoined matches (expiry policy) | Edge Case | No | **Deferred** — no auto-expiry in V1, creator must cancel manually |\n| 7 | Edge case: wallet disconnect during flip/settlement | Edge Case | No | **In scope** — frontend error handling checklist item covers this |\n| 8 | Edge case: VRF request timeout or failure handling | Edge Case | No | **Deferred** — mock oracle in V1, MagicBlock VRF integration deferred |\n\n## Refinement Decisions (2026-02-17)\n\n| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n|----------|--------|-----------|\n| Tier amounts | Frontend/spec values canonical | Iron→Diamond, [0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0] SOL. On-chain shared crate updated to match. |\n| Coin side discriminants | 0/1 (on-chain canonical) | heads=0, tails=1. Game-engine updated to match. |\n| VRF approach | Mock oracle for V1 | Test keypair signs resolve_match. MagicBlock deferred. |\n| Platform program | Included in spec | CPI for player profile updates on settlement. |\n| Spec scope | On-chain + engine + frontend | Audio, fairness UI, animation polish, Playwright tests deferred. |\n| PDA structure | Rewrite game-engine | Delete old BOLT ECS PDAs, use simple creator-based PDAs matching on-chain. |\n\n## Refinement Carry-Forward (Pivot)\n\n- [ ] Lock Coinflip fairness proof contract fields and verification path for selected VRF provider.\n- [ ] Confirm determinism boundary: contract derives final outcome from verifiable on-chain/public inputs only.\n- [ ] Add explicit timeout/refund acceptance checks aligned to shared lifecycle invariants.\n- [ ] Reconfirm idempotency/replay protection requirements for join, resolve, and payout/claim paths.\n- [ ] Add failure-mode acceptance checks for VRF callback delay/failure and pause-state behavior.\n\n## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` in coinflip `chain.ts` for claimable/unresolved matches.\n- [ ] Ensure claimable query covers player as creator OR opponent, `claimed == false`, and non-terminal phases that can still be claimed.\n- [ ] Expose claimable matches in frontend UX (for example, \"Pending Claims\" or equivalent unresolved matches list).\n\n## Notes\n\n- Source material (COINFLIP.md) is well-specified for core flows\n- All blocking items resolved during /refine interview (2026-02-17)\n- 12 granular checklist items in spec, ordered by dependency\n- 8 functional requirements extracted, all with acceptance criteria\n- Validation plan cove