{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019Qpn5Vr6ihjzWTigcdfpvc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification Quality Checklist: 003 Platform Core Systems\n     2→\n     3→**Purpose**: Validate specification completeness and quality before implementation\n     4→**Created**: 2026-02-12\n     5→**Spec**: [spec.md](spec.md)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Content Quality\n    10→\n    11→- [x] No implementation details (languages, frameworks, APIs)\n    12→- [x] Focused on user value and business needs\n    13→- [x] Written for non-technical stakeholders\n    14→- [x] All mandatory sections completed\n    15→\n    16→## Requirement Completeness\n    17→\n    18→- [ ] No [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] markers remain\n    19→- [x] Requirements are testable and unambiguous\n    20→- [x] Success criteria are measurable\n    21→- [x] Success criteria are technology-agnostic\n    22→- [x] Acceptance criteria are defined\n    23→- [ ] Edge cases are identified\n    24→- [x] Scope is clearly bounded\n    25→- [x] Dependencies and assumptions identified\n    26→\n    27→## Feature Readiness\n    28→\n    29→- [x] All functional requirements have clear acceptance criteria\n    30→- [x] User scenarios cover primary flows\n    31→- [x] Feature meets measurable outcomes defined in Success Criteria\n    32→- [x] No implementation details leak into specification\n    33→\n    34→---\n    35→\n    36→## Open Items\n    37→\n    38→| # | Item | Category | Blocking? |\n    39→|---|------|----------|-----------|\n    40→| 1 | Platform fee percentage inconsistency (2.0-2.2% vs 3%) | FR-4 | Yes |\n    41→| 2 | Contract files not identified (wallet adapter, UI exports) | Contract | Yes |\n    42→| 3 | Maximum flexible bet limit undefined (may vary by game/player) | FR-3 | No |\n    43→| 4 | Provably fair API endpoint - is it required for V1? | FR-5 | No |\n    44→| 5 | Account system details undefined (optional account creation) | FR-8 | No |\n    45→| 6 | CSV export for game history - is it V1? | FR-7 | No |\n    46→| 7 | Edge case: wallet disconnect during active transaction | Edge Case | No |\n    47→| 8 | Edge case: stale balance display after external wallet activity | Edge Case | No |\n    48→| 9 | Monitoring tooling selection undefined | FR-9 | No |\n    49→| 10 | Rate limiting thresholds undefined | FR-9 | No |\n    50→\n    51→## Cross-Game Refinement Obligations (Pivot)\n    52→\n    53→- [ ] Standard proof envelope is defined once for all games (proof type, proof hash/ref, proof_version).\n    54→- [ ] Shared lifecycle invariants are reflected in every game spec checklist (timeout, pause, fee, refund).\n    55→- [ ] Shared idempotency/replay protection expectations are documented for all game actions.\n    56→- [ ] Shared observability/event requirements are defined for phase transitions and settlement outcomes.\n    57→- [ ] Provider decisions are locked and propagated to game specs (VRF provider, oracle policy, commit-reveal baseline).\n    58→\n    59→## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n    60→\n    61→- [ ] Define canonical lifecycle event envelope and names for cross-game transitions (at minimum create, join, cancel, timeout, settled).\n    62→- [ ] Confirm event-driven consumption path for frontend/indexer while preserving account polling as fallback.\n    63→- [ ] Decide whether `settled_at` should remain event/indexer-derived (default) or be persisted in long-lived accounts for games that do not close immediately.\n    64→\n    65→## Notes\n    66→\n    67→- Platform Core is cross-cutting (Phase 0-3), not a single deliverable\n    68→- Some items here (wallet, tiers, fees) are prerequisites for Coinflip (Phase 1)\n    69→- Others (history, profile, ops controls) ship in Phase 3\n    70→- Implementation should be incremental: build what Coinflip needs first, expand for Lord of the RNGs, complete in Phase 3\n    71→- 9 functional requirements extracted covering the full platform surface\n    72→- Deferred items explicitly excluded: custodial balances, rakeback distribution, loyalty gating, token utility, leaderboard rewards\n    73→- Game history CSV export mentioned in PLATFORM.md but may be post-V1 - needs decision\n    74→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"7f022bd1-45a0-425c-8dde-612f4e2ec100","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/003-platform-core/checklist.md","content":"# Specification Quality Checklist: 003 Platform Core Systems\n\n**Purpose**: Validate specification completeness and quality before implementation\n**Created**: 2026-02-12\n**Spec**: [spec.md](spec.md)\n\n---\n\n## Content Quality\n\n- [x] No implementation details (languages, frameworks, APIs)\n- [x] Focused on user value and business needs\n- [x] Written for non-technical stakeholders\n- [x] All mandatory sections completed\n\n## Requirement Completeness\n\n- [ ] No [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] markers remain\n- [x] Requirements are testable and unambiguous\n- [x] Success criteria are measurable\n- [x] Success criteria are technology-agnostic\n- [x] Acceptance criteria are defined\n- [ ] Edge cases are identified\n- [x] Scope is clearly bounded\n- [x] Dependencies and assumptions identified\n\n## Feature Readiness\n\n- [x] All functional requirements have clear acceptance criteria\n- [x] User scenarios cover primary flows\n- [x] Feature meets measurable outcomes defined in Success Criteria\n- [x] No implementation details leak into specification\n\n---\n\n## Open Items\n\n| # | Item | Category | Blocking? |\n|---|------|----------|-----------|\n| 1 | Platform fee percentage inconsistency (2.0-2.2% vs 3%) | FR-4 | Yes |\n| 2 | Contract files not identified (wallet adapter, UI exports) | Contract | Yes |\n| 3 | Maximum flexible bet limit undefined (may vary by game/player) | FR-3 | No |\n| 4 | Provably fair API endpoint - is it required for V1? | FR-5 | No |\n| 5 | Account system details undefined (optional account creation) | FR-8 | No |\n| 6 | CSV export for game history - is it V1? | FR-7 | No |\n| 7 | Edge case: wallet disconnect during active transaction | Edge Case | No |\n| 8 | Edge case: stale balance display after external wallet activity | Edge Case | No |\n| 9 | Monitoring tooling selection undefined | FR-9 | No |\n| 10 | Rate limiting thresholds undefined | FR-9 | No |\n\n## Cross-Game Refinement Obligations (Pivot)\n\n- [ ] Standard proof envelope is defined once for all games (proof type, proof hash/ref, proof_version).\n- [ ] Shared lifecycle invariants are reflected in every game spec checklist (timeout, pause, fee, refund).\n- [ ] Shared idempotency/replay protection expectations are documented for all game actions.\n- [ ] Shared observability/event requirements are defined for phase transitions and settlement outcomes.\n- [ ] Provider decisions are locked and propagated to game specs (VRF provider, oracle policy, commit-reveal baseline).\n\n## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] Define canonical lifecycle event envelope and names for cross-game transitions (at minimum create, join, cancel, timeout, settled).\n- [ ] Confirm event-driven consumption path for frontend/indexer while preserving account polling as fallback.\n- [ ] Decide whether `settled_at` should remain event/indexer-derived (default) or be persisted in long-lived accounts for games that do not close immediately.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Platform Core is cross-cutting (Phase 0-3), not a single deliverable\n- Some items here (wallet, tiers, fees) are prerequisites for Coinflip (Phase 1)\n- Others (history, profile, ops controls) ship in Phase 3\n- Implementation should be incremental: build what Coinflip needs first, expand for Lord of the RNGs, complete in Phase 3\n- 9 functional requirements extracted covering the full platform surface\n- Deferred items explicitly excluded: custodial balances, rakeback distribution, loyalty gating, token utility, leaderboard rewards\n- Game history CSV export mentioned in PLATFORM.md but may be post-V1 - needs decision\n","numLines":74,"startLine":1,"totalLines":74}}}
