\n    45→| 6 | No contract files for deferred games | Contract | No (deferred) |\n    46→\n    47→## Refinement Carry-Forward (Pivot)\n    48→\n    49→- [ ] Lock Lord of the RNGs fairness proof contract fields and verification flow for selected VRF provider.\n    50→- [ ] Confirm determinism boundary: wheel outcome and payouts derive solely from verified VRF output and on-chain state.\n    51→- [ ] Specify timeout/refund behavior for unresolved rounds and countdown cancellation paths.\n    52→- [ ] Define replay/idempotency protections for entry purchase, resolve, and payout distribution.\n    53→- [ ] Add failure-mode acceptance checks for low-player rounds, disconnections, and VRF resolution failures.\n    54→\n    55→## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n    56→\n    57→- [ ] Extend platform profile update path with a game discriminator before/with Lord implementation.\n    58→- [ ] Update shared CPI helper contract to carry game identity for per-game attribution in profile/history.\n    59→- [ ] Add acceptance checks that settlement updates both aggregate and per-game stats correctly.\n    60→\n    61→## Notes\n    62→\n    63→- Source material (LORD_OF_THE_RNGS.md) is well-specified\n    64→- Simple game mechanics (buy entries -> spin -> winner takes all)\n    65→- 8 functional requirements extracted\n    66→- Multi-entry mechanic is the distinguishing feature - probability math is straightforward\n    67→- VRF reuse from Coinflip simplifies implementation\n    68→- Fewer blocking items than V1 games since it shares infrastructure\n    69→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71f3d66f-916b-4438-95fb-e3b573af6aa8","uuid":"7a334522-b9bc-48e2-8a47-9fef9c3f567b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/checklist.md","content":"# Specification Quality Checklist: 101 Lord of the RNGs\n\n**Purpose**: Validate specification completeness and quality before implementation\n**Cr