low-player rounds, disconnections, and VRF resolution failures.\n\n## Gap Analysis Carry-Forward (004 Shared Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] Extend platform profile update path with a game discriminator before/with Lord implementation.\n- [ ] Update shared CPI helper contract to carry game identity for per-game attribution in profile/history.\n- [ ] Add acceptance checks that settlement updates both aggregate and per-game stats correctly.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Source material (LORD_OF_THE_RNGS.md) is well-specified\n- Simple game mechanics (buy entries -> spin -> winner takes all)\n- 8 functional requirements extracted\n- Multi-entry mechanic is the distinguishing feature - probability math is straightforward\n- VRF reuse from Coinflip simplifies implementation\n- Fewer blocking items than V1 games since it shares infrastructure\n","numLines":69,"startLine":1,"totalLines":69}}}
